.TH 9p-getattr 5 "@META_DATE@" "@META_ALIAS@" "@META_NAME@"
.SH NAME
9p getattr \- get file status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
size[4] Tgetattr tag[2] fid[4] request_mask[8]
size[4] Rgetattr tag[2] valid[8] qid[13] mode[4] nlink[8] uid[4] gid[4]
                 rdev[8] size[8] blksize]8] blocks[8]
                 atime_sec[8] atime_nsec[8] mtime_sec[8] mtime_nsec[8]
                 ctime_sec[8] ctime_nsec[8] btime_sec[8] btime_nsec[8]
                 gen[8] data_version[8]
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
getattr requests file attributes identified in request_mask[8]
for the file referenced by fid.  The same bit values are
used in both valid[8] and request_mask[8] (see below).
.TP
\fIvalid[8]\fR
A bitmask indicating which fields in the response are valid.
See below for bit values.
.TP
\fIqid[13]\fR
The qid of the file.
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_INO (0x100) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fImode[4]\fR
Permission and flags
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_MODE (0x1) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fInlink[8]\fR
Number of hard links
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_NLINK (0x2) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIuid[4]\fR
User id of owner
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_UID (0x4) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIgid[4]\fR
Group ID of owner
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_GID (0x8) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIrdev[8]\fR
Device ID (if special file)
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_RDEV (0x10) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIsize[8]\fR
Size, in bytes
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_SIZE (0x200) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIblksize[8]\fR
Block size for file system IO.
.br
Always must be valid (no mask bit).
.TP
\fIblocks[8]\fR
Number of file system blocks allocated
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_BLOCKS (0x400) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIatime_sec[8]\fR, \fIatime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last access, seconds and nanoseconds.
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_ATIME (0x20) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fImtime_sec[8]\fR, \fImtime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last modification, seconds and nanoseconds.
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_MTIME (0x40) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIctime_sec[8]\fR, \fIctime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last status change, seconds and nanoseconds.
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_CTIME (0x80) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIbtime_sec[8]\fR, \fIbtime_nsec[8]\fR
Time of last backup, seconds and nanoseconds (not currently used).
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_BTIME (0x800) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIgen[8]\fR
Inode generation number.
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_GEN (0x1000) is set in valid[8].
.TP
\fIdata_version[8]\fR
Reserved for future use.
.br
Valid if P9_GETATTR_DATA_VERSION (0x2000) is set in valid[8].
.SH ORIGIN
9P2000.L
.SH SEE ALSO
9p-intro(5)
